 22-Ti- 48 ORNL Resonance Evaluation Including Covariance         2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
 L. C. Leal, K. Guber, G. Arbanas and D. Wiarda                   2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
Resolved resonance parameter evaluation for Ti-48 was done with   2231 1451
the computer code SAMMY.[ref1] Capture and transmission           2231 1451
measurements for enriched Ti-48 and natural titanium were done    2231 1451
at the Oak Ridge Electron Linear Accelerator (ORELA) of the Oak   2231 1451
Ridge National Laboratory. The neutron transmission and capture   2231 1451
data were measured in the energy range from 10 eV to 500 keV.     2231 1451
The transmission data were measured at the 80-meter flight-path,  2231 1451
whereas the 40-meter flight-path was used for the capture cross   2231 1451
section measurements. Since there are no capture cross section    2231 1451
measurements availble in the resonance region the ORELA data were 2231 1451
important for determining the shape and the uncertainty in the    2231 1451
capture cross section. The resonance evaluation for Ti-48 was     2231 1451
done in the energy range from 10-5 eV to 400 keV. Thermal cross   2231 1451
section data available in the EXFOR data system were also added   2231 1451
in the evaluation.                                                2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
Thermal direct-semidirect (DSD) capture on Ti-48 was computed     2231 1451
using the computer code CUPIDO developed by F.S. Dietrich (LLNL)  2231 1451
[ref2].  The thermal DSD was found to be 0.55 barns, using the    2231 1451
single-particle spectroscopic factors from [ref3].                2231 1451
Together with the  resonant thermal capture of 1.144 barns, the   2231 1451
computed DSD was insufficient to account for the measured total   2231 1451
thermal capture cross section of 8.32 +- 0.16 b.  Therefore, a    2231 1451
loosely bound state was introduced into the parameter set, and    2231 1451
its parameters were fitted to the total capture data.  The        2231 1451
computed DSD capture was not used in the fitting process.         2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
A set of resonance parameter describing the experimental data     2231 1451
was obtained. Resonance parameter covariance matrices were also   2231 1451
obtained in the SAMMY evaluation process. The Ti-48 evaluation    2231 1451
was done in the energy region 10-5 eV 400 keV.                    2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
