1. Cross Sections, MF3, MT1, MT16, 22, 28, 102, 103, 107          2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
First GNASH calculation was performed to the Ti48(n,xng) data     2231 1451
from GEANIE experiments [Da07], and extended the same             2231 1451
parametrization to other isotopes. The level density              2231 1451
parameters were often adjusted to reproduce experimental data     2231 1451
of (n,2n), (n,p), and (n,alpha) reactions if available.           2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
The neutron radiative capture cross section was evaluated         2231 1451
with the CoH and DSD codes. The gamma-ray strength function       2231 1451
was renormalized to reproduce experimental data in the            2231 1451
20 - 50 keV energy range.                                         2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
The total cross section data from 367 keV to 6 MeV were obtained  2231 1451
by the least-squares method to experimental data available.       2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
2. Elastic Scattering Angular Distribution, MF4, MT2              2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
It was found that the angular distribution in the resonance       2231 1451
range (up to 1MeV) is crucial for criticality benchmark           2231 1451
tests which have Ti reflectors. We adopted ENDF/B-VI data         2231 1451
up to 4 MeV, which are based on experimental data.                2231 1451
Above 4 MeV, the angular distribution was calculated with         2231 1451
the optical model.                                                2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
3. Covariances, MF33                                              2231 1451
                                                                  2231 1451
All covariance data were calculated with the KALMAN code.         2231 1451
Typical uncertainties obtained are 1-3 % for the total,           2231 1451
10-30 % for the capture, etc. The covariance data for             2231 1451
(n,d) and (n,t) are not given, because they are very small        2231 1451
cross sections.                                                   2231 1451
